  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity building for the Ombudsman&apos;s office to be better prepared to mediate in environmental conflicts and supervise the proper enforcement of environmental norms/ Peru, whole country.
Environmental conflicts are multiplying across the country as a consequence of past bad practices by private companies, mainly in the mining industry, but also as a consequence of the already present effects of climate change, like the growing scarcity of water. In many cases, it is a matter of lack of dialogue or inadequate channels for it between entrepreneurs and local people. The ombudsman&apos;s office has become a key actor for preventing conflicts as it is sometimes the only one that is trusted and respected by all parts.</narrative>
  </description>
